    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> mince</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is browning, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Slice <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red chilli[es] </strong>into rounds (save these for garnish!)<strong> </strong>and finely chop the rest</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the mince has browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>, <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) to the pan and cook for 2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> with your <strong>red chilli relish </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for a further 2 min or until sticky and the mince is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style sticky chilli mince</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the mince is cooking, combine the <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> in a bowl with the juice of <strong>half </strong>your <strong>lime[s]</strong>, your <strong>fish sauce </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style dressing</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> mooli slaw mix </strong>to the <strong>Thai-style dressing </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai-style slaw</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, strip your <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stems, discard the stems</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is cooked, add it to the <strong>Thai-style slaw </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>rice salad</strong></p><p>Cut the<strong> remaining lime</strong> into 1 wedge per person</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-style-sticky-chilli-lean-beef-and-brown-rice-salad/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Thai-style sticky chilli mince </strong>over the <strong>fragrant</strong> <strong>rice salad</strong>, topped with the <strong>chopped coriander</strong>, <strong>mint leaves</strong> and <strong>crispy onions</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>reserved chilli rounds</strong> (not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)<strong> </strong>and a <strong>lime wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
